This is the pipeline where i created end to end by using jobs inside databricks,in jobs and pipeline i created one job, in that job i divided 3 tasks interlink with each other.
->In first task ingestion will takes from sourceFile here i used autoloader concept to pick only latest file and provided usermanagedfile event to avoid listing and for this task i have added file arrival trigger also to get benifit of event trigger.(by using file arrival trigger whenever the new file landed into source automatically databricks runs its job without any events service ,through this we can avoid infrastructure and usage of other service), Through this we achieved the incremental file load from source systems.

code of task1:-
raw_df=(
    spark.readStream.format('cloudFiles')
        .option('cloudFiles.format','csv')
        .option('cloudFiles.schemaLocation',schema_location)
        .option('cloudFiles.schemaEvolutionMode','addNewColumns')
        .option('header','true')
        .option('cloudFiles.inferColumnTypes','true')
        .option('mode','PERMISSIVE')
        .option('badRecordsPath',badRecord_Path)
        .option("rescuedDataColumn", "_rescued_data")
        .option("cloudFiles.useManagedFileEvents", "true")
        .option("ignoreLeadingWhiteSpace", "true")
        .option("ignoreTrailingWhiteSpace", "true")

        .load(source_path)

)



from pyspark.sql.functions import current_timestamp,input_file_name

final_df=(
    raw_df.withColumn('ingestion_time',current_timestamp())
          #.withColumn('source_file',input_file_name())
         
)

query=(
    final_df.writeStream
    .format('delta')
    .option('checkpointLocation',checkpoint_location)
    .option('mergeSchema','true')
    .outputMode('append')
    .trigger(availableNow=True)
    .toTable(target_table)
)
query.awaitTermination()
here i used trigger(availableNow=True) because once we get all files, we dont need to trigger this continuosly withthat we can reduce cost of compute.mergeschema also added incase if schema changes here

