instead of that let them allow in bronze, however bronze will maintain history if data in real projetcs(actual raw data), and in silver layer we will check duplications and remove them. This is the best approach 

.option("cloudFiles.allowOverwrites", "false) use this one also useful

Auto Loader will avoid ingesting the same file path again using checkpoint. But if duplicate files arrive with different file names/paths, Auto Loader will ingest them as new files. To overcome this in real projects, keep Bronze as raw history, then deduplicate in Silver using business keys, record hash, and Delta MERGE. Also maintain a file/record audit table to track duplicate files and duplicate records.
